  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were just dropped there across the street from the synagogue, from the shul, which was only the second or third building out of the street-- at the beginning of the street.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there they were, totally lost, obviously being uprooted suddenly and without-- not only not given any preparation, but totally lost.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because they were given no idea of what their fate was to have been.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And in, in our town by that time, there were very few young Jewish men around.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because most of the others had been hauled away long before to the so-called labor auxiliaries of the Hungarian army, which basically meant really being cannon fodder or, or mine detectors for the Germans in-- on the Eastern Front.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I must have been one of maybe a dozen young Jews of, of my age, with the exception of perhaps some of the more Hasidic Jews, who somehow managed to escape being called up to the labor auxiliary.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I wasn't called up, because I was registered at some other place.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And, and then they-- eventually, they transferred my registration to Kisvarda.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in Kisvarda by that time, they weren't calling up people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because obviously, we were already consigned to annihilation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But some of the other young people of my age whose registration was in some other town, particularly in Budapest, they were called up, so that in effect, we have had no able-bodied young Jews in the city with really exception of maybe a dozen or, or, or maybe two dozen people.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And when I say able-bodied, I don't even mean people who were physically able-bodied but who were mentally [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] in, in the position and had the attitude of attempting to try to help.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
